# Cloudflare Pages response headers for the Control Center phone PWA.
#
# Flutter copies everything under web/ into build/web/, and Cloudflare Pages
# reads this file from the deployed asset root — so these headers apply to the
# hosted PWA (they are NOT applied by `flutter run -d chrome` locally, which is
# deliberate: a strict CSP there would block the dev server's hot-reload socket).
#
# Why this exists (audit finding #4): the pairing PSK is persisted in cleartext
# in IndexedDB. With no CSP, any script that gains a foothold on this origin (a
# compromised transitive dep, a hijacked deploy, a malicious extension, a future
# XSS) could read it and POST it out. The Content-Security-Policy below removes
# the network egress an exfiltrator needs and locks down the script surface.
#
# Flutter-web specifics baked in:
#   * script-src 'wasm-unsafe-eval'      — CanvasKit/skwasm WebAssembly.
#   * https://www.gstatic.com            — Flutter fetches CanvasKit from gstatic
#                                          by default. If you self-host CanvasKit
#                                          (FLUTTER_WEB_CANVASKIT_URL / a local
#                                          build), drop gstatic from script-src
#                                          AND connect-src.
#   * style-src 'unsafe-inline'          — Flutter injects inline <style>.
#   * connect-src 'self' wss:            — same-origin asset fetches + the WebRTC
#                                          signaling broker (wss). The broker host
#                                          is operator-configured, so it can't be
#                                          pinned statically here; for the tightest
#                                          posture replace `wss:` with your exact
#                                          broker origin (e.g. wss://broker.example.com)
#                                          so a foothold can't open wss://evil.
#   Note: STUN/TURN ICE is not governed by connect-src, so STUN needs no entry.
#   * base-uri 'self'                     — REQUIRED, do NOT tighten to 'none'.
#                                          main.dart calls usePathUrlStrategy(), whose
#                                          PathUrlStrategy reads the <base href="/">
#                                          element to derive route paths. `base-uri
#                                          'none'` neutralizes <base>, so the engine
#                                          reads an empty href and throws "The base
#                                          href has to end with a '/' to work
#                                          correctly", aborting boot before runApp.
#                                          'self' permits only a same-origin base
#                                          (the `/` Flutter emits), so it can't be
#                                          hijacked to redirect relative URLs off-origin.

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'wasm-unsafe-eval' https://www.gstatic.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: blob:; font-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self' wss: https://www.gstatic.com; worker-src 'self' blob:; manifest-src 'self'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'none'
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(self), display-capture=(self), geolocation=(), payment=(), usb=(), accelerometer=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
